    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Territories that are defined in United States law as under the control of the government of the USA, and where fundamental rights apply as a matter of law, but certain other constitutional rights are not available. Examples are Puerto Rico and Guam.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
